<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="14" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="13.[189,454,824,850]" box="[189,454,824,850]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,454,824,850]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,454,824,850]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Differential diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="13.[189,1399,871,1036]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
<taxonomicName authority="Barkalov &amp; Ståhls, 2022" authorityName="Barkalov &amp; Ståhls" authorityYear="2022" box="[189,635,871,897]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Cheilosia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="albipicta" status="sp. nov." subGenus="Montanocheila">
<emphasis box="[189,305,871,897]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Cheilosia</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[325,508,871,897]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Montanocheila</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[528,635,871,897]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">albipicta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[646,742,871,897]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is most similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Barkalov &amp; Ståhls, 2022" authorityName="Barkalov &amp; Ståhls" authorityYear="2022" box="[979,1140,871,897]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Cheilosia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="picta" status="sp. nov." subGenus="Montanocheila">
<emphasis box="[979,1007,871,897]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">C.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[1027,1060,872,897]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">M.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[1080,1140,872,897]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">picta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1151,1249,871,897]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, and can be distinguished by the black pilosity of 
<taxonomicName authority="Barkalov &amp; Ståhls, 2022" authorityName="Barkalov &amp; Ståhls" authorityYear="2022" box="[647,742,906,932]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Cheilosia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="picta" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[647,742,906,932]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">C. picta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[750,843,906,932]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
laterally on tergites III–IV, while 
<taxonomicName authority="Barkalov &amp; Ståhls, 2022" authorityName="Barkalov &amp; Ståhls" authorityYear="2022" box="[1257,1399,906,932]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Cheilosia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="albipicta" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1257,1399,906,932]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">C. albipicta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[189,280,941,967]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
has black pilosity only on postero-lateral margin of tergite III. 
<taxonomicName authority="Barkalov &amp; Ståhls, 2022" authorityName="Barkalov &amp; Ståhls" authorityYear="2022" box="[1028,1253,940,966]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Cheilosia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="albipicta" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1028,1253,940,966]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Cheilosia albipicta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1260,1352,941,967]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
has a distinct shape of the superior lobe of the male genitalia, not shared with any other member of the subgenus (e.g., 
<figureCitation box="[372,497,1010,1036]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="14.[189,233,1892,1918]" captionTargetBox="[261,1306,352,1835]" captionTargetId="figure-14@14.[261,1326,265,1855]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="Fig. 3. Cheilosia (Montanocheila) albipicta sp. nov., holotype, ♂ (CSCA). A. Head, lateral view. B. Antenna, lateral view of pedicel and basoflagellomere. C. Tip of wing. D. Surstylus and gonocercus, lateral view. E. Aedeagus and aedeagal apodeme, lateral view. F. Superior lobe of hypandrium, lateral view. Scale bars indicated in drawings." pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Fig. 3D–F</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="14" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="13.[189,324,1076,1102]" box="[189,324,1076,1102]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,324,1076,1102]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,324,1076,1102]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Etymology</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="13.[189,1398,1122,1183]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
The specific epithet is from the Latin ‘ 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Barkalov &amp; Ståhls" authorityYear="2022" box="[660,767,1122,1148]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Cheilosia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="albipicta">
<emphasis box="[660,767,1122,1148]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">albipicta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
’ meaning ‘white patterned’, referring to the whitish pilosity.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
